============================================================
=====                   Introduction                    ====
============================================================
This package makes use docsim-htmlproc, docsim-shingle and lsa to generate
document similarity measurements.

============================================================
=====                   Usage                           ====
============================================================
Apply shingling algorithm to bunch of data:
    mvn test
    mvn -Pshingle
    mvn -Pshingle -Dexec.args="-c config-file -o output-file"

    If you want to change default configurations of shingling algorithm,
    modify file:
        ./src/main/resources/training.config

Input data source (generated by using package docsim-data) is specified in config
file by property *datafile*. The common flow is to use docsim-data to retrieve
data first and then use this package to apply shingling and lsa algorithms to
the data.

Apply shingling algorithm to a pair of docs:
    mvn test
    mvn -Ppair -Dexec.args="-url1 http://address1 -url2 http://address2"

Analyze data:
    mvn test
    mvn -Panalyze
    mvn -Panalyze -Dexec.args="-h"
    mvn -Panalyze -Dexec.args="-i results_firsttwo.txt -o results_summary.txt"

Convert data to Arff format (can be used by Weka):
    mvn -Ptodtree -Dexec.args="-h"
    mvn -Ptodtree -Dexec.args="-i results_allpairs.txt -o dtree"


